# ============================================================================
# §Doc-only — KEL reshape: data-local detection + the manifest/spine model
# ============================================================================
# The KEL primitive docs reconciled to the post-reshape canon (event-shape +
# protocol-doctrine): divergence detection is data-local (the verifier walks
# retained branches; the witness beacon propagates, never decides), so the
# federation-decides framing and its vocabulary are retired:
#   federation-irreconcilable  — the federation does not pronounce a verdict;
#     a fork with >= 2 privileged branches reads disputed: by a data-local walk;
#   effective-SAID synthetics divergent:{prefix} / irreconcilable:{prefix}  —
#     replaced by forked:{prefix} (reconcilable / pending) and disputed:{prefix}
#     (terminal). Bare "divergent" / "irreconcilable" stay live (the per-node
#     fork state and the fork classification), so only the colon-synthetic forms
#     are forbidden;
#   policy_satisfied  — the verifier token reports the structural-validity
#     result, not a policy signal (authorization is structural; policy lives on
#     documents);
#   RecoveryRecord  — a repair commits its archival tails in folded.forks[],
#     not a separate audit-row type;
#   witnessParams / witnessThreshold / witnessSelectionSize  — the witness
#     config rides the `witnesses` manifest role as a { threshold, signers } SAD.
federation-irreconcilable
divergent:\{prefix\}
irreconcilable:\{prefix\}
\bpolicy_satisfied\b
\bRecoveryRecord\b
\bwitnessParams\b
\bwitnessThreshold\b
\bwitnessSelectionSize\b

# ============================================================================
# §Doc-only — Fed→Wit + folded→folds remodel
# ============================================================================
# The federation-mutation kind Fed merged into the one witness/federation kind
# Wit (a user federation rebind on an Icp-rooted KEL; federation governance on
# an Fcp-rooted KEL). Founder genesis is Fcp → Rot (the Rot anchors the
# federation IEL's Fcp marker) — there is no founder Fed/Wit. The manifest role
# folded was renamed folds (dual-readable like anchors/delegates). The prose
# verb "folded" (the content run folded since the prior seal) stays live — only
# the role name and its dotted accessors regress, so forbid the role/accessor
# forms (`folded`, folded.forks, folded.canonical), never the bare verb.
# \bFed\b does not match "federation" (word boundary fails at the trailing e).
\bFed\b
`folded`
folded\.forks
folded\.canonical

# ============================================================================
# §Doc-only — root-pointing repair model (forks = roots, not tips)
# ============================================================================
# A repair's forks names each losing branch's ROOT — its first divergent event,
# condemning the whole subtree (growth-proof) — never its tip. The tip-pointing
# model and its apparatus (a re-freeze on an under-covering repair; a follow-up
# repair required to catch post-repair growth) are retired: an under-covering
# content repair is ACCEPTED (missed content inerts below the seal, growth dead
# by descent). Bare "tip" stays live everywhere (chain tip, branch tip, the
# SEL's IEL-anchored tip); only the forks-entry collocations and the retired
# apparatus regress.
archived[- ]branch tips?
`forks` tips
\bsecond repair\b
re-freez
re-frozen

